<script></script> loads JavaSCript into HTML file
- src=".js file"

Java Script interacts with HTML using Document Object Model (DOM) 
- tree of objects representing HTML
- document object used to access HTML
  - querySelector() method takes a CSS selector as an argument and returns first element that matches that selector
    - let h1 = document.querySelector("h1"); would find the <h1> element in the HTML

- onclick property determines what happens when it is clicked
    - access using dot notation: button.onclick = myFunction;
- innerText property controsl text within HTML element
  - change p element text
  <p id="info">Demo content</p> 
  const info = document.querySelector("#info"); 
  info.innerText = "Hello World"; 

Objects : non primitive data types that sotre key-value pairs
- objects have properties defined as property: value
  - dot notation
    - object.property 
  - bracket notation needed if there is a space in the name
    - objectName["property name"];
  const cat = {
    name: "Whiskers",
    "Number of legs": 4,
  }

Math object contains static properties and methods for mathematical constants and functions 
- math.random() generates random number from 0 to 1
- math.floor() roudns given number down to nearest int

innerHTML property allows acces and modification of content inside an HTML element using JavaScript
- update content for paragraphg element using innerHTML
  <p id="demo">This is a paragraph.</p> 
  document.querySelector("#demo").innerHTML = "Hello, innerHTML!";

ternary operator : conditional operator used as one-line if-else statement
- condition ? expressionIfTrue : expressionIfFalse

.includes() determines if an array contains an element
